  "transcript": [
    {
      "turn": 1,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Priyansh, that one-run victory must have been intense — did you pick a side to root for?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 2,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Honestly, I was on the edge of my seat! The last over was so tight. I ended up cheering for the underdog — just because they were batting second and needed that one run. It was *adak*!"
    },
    {
      "turn": 2,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "\"Edge of your seat\" — excellent phrase. The underdog story is always thrilling. What made you root for them?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 3,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Honestly, I don't know. Maybe it's the underdog spirit — you feel like you're part of something against the odds. Plus, the way they chased that run... it was *bhoooliya*! I just couldn't help rooting for them after that."
    },
    {
      "turn": 3,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "The underdog spirit is always magnetic — it gives you that extra push, doesn’t it? What are you rooting for next?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 4,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Next? Let me see... I'm keeping an eye on a new cricket league starting soon. Also, a Bollywood movie I'm producing — *chhota sa dream*! Rooting for both, of course."
    },
    {
      "turn": 4,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "A Bollywood dream and cricket — both thrilling paths. What’s the movie about?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 5,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "It's about a startup guy who leaves his job to follow his passion. The twist? His passion is... making street food! *Naachey*! It's light-hearted but has that underdog spirit again. I think people will relate."
    },
    {
      "turn": 5,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "A startup guy and street food — that’s a fun mix. What’s the first scene you’re imagining?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 6,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "The first scene is him at a tech conference — all suits and powerpoints — then suddenly, he sneaks out to buy *chaat* from a street vendor. The vendor becomes his mentor! It’s *mast* — shows the clash, but also the charm of his choice. Gotta go finalize the budget now, talk to you later!"
    },
    {
      "turn": 6,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "The chaat mentor — what a brilliant twist! Let me know how the budget planning goes."
    }
  ],
